I have unit tests where all scenarios except one use a set of mock requests and responses. I'd like to just do 1 beforeEach that applies to all tests, then override the responses for the 1 special case scenario.

Desired:

```
beforeEach(function() {
    //set up mock requests/responses
});

describe('normal case', function() { ... });
describe('normal case', function() { ... });
describe('normal case', function() { ... });
describe('normal case', function() {
    describe('special case', function() {
        beforeEach(function() {
            //override mock requests/responses
        });
    });
});
```

As far as I can tell, there is no good way to override (since 'when' appends to the 'definitions' array: https://github.com/angular/angular.js/blob/7aef2d54e0a48fae18a289813f699962d8310565/src/ngMock/angular-mocks.js#L1240 and the iteration always finds the first match: https://github.com/angular/angular.js/blob/7aef2d54e0a48fae18a289813f699962d8310565/src/ngMock/angular-mocks.js#L1186-L1196 ), so I'd have to restructure to do something like this:

```
describe('normal cases', function() {
    beforeEach(function() {
        //set up mock requests/responses
    });

    describe('normal case', function() { ... });
    describe('normal case', function() { ... });
    describe('normal case', function() { ... });
});

describe('special cases', function() {
    beforeEach(function() {
        //set up special case mock requests/responses
    });
    describe('special case', function() { ... });
});
```

Just a thought. Would be more than happy to put in a PR
